<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-62-0927 </DOCNO><TEXT>This paper presents an extensive survey of literature about wind energyand wind machines, their design and their applications. The paper intendsto provide those who plan for energy policy with thorough informationabout this renewable type of energy and the available machines that convertwind energy into useful mechanical or electrical work. The machines whichare available at present range from the simple Savonius rotor to thepowerful multi-blade windmills. The advantages and shortcomings of alltypes are discussed here.</TEXT></DOC>